      • packResourcePack

        public static java.util.HashMap<PackFormat,java.io.File> packResourcePack(java.io.File resourcePackFolder,
                                                                          java.io.File outputFolder,
                                                                          MCPackrLogger logger)
                                                                   throws java.io.IOException
        Packs a resource pack into a zip for each pack format.
        Parameters:
        resourcePackFolder - The base folder of the resource pack, which should include a pack.mcmeta file.
        outputFolder - The folder where the zips should be generated in.
        logger - The logger. Use MCPackrNullLogger for no logging, MCPackrStdoutLogger for logging to `stdout`, or create your own logger extending MCPackrLogger.
        Returns:
        The files that have been generated or empty on failure.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - When a file is not found, or could not be written to, etc.
